│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs inside BoUpSLP::computeMinimumValueSizes(), specifically     │
│ when evaluating lambdas that iterate over TreeEntry::UserTreeIndices. The     │
│ stack shows a segfault at InstructionsState::valid() invoked via              │
│ TreeEntry::hasState(), but the immediate cause is dereferencing a null        │
│ TreeEntry pointer (this=0x0) from EI.UserTE in the lambda. EdgeInfo default   │
│ constructor produces EdgeInfo() with UserTE==nullptr. Root (and possibly      │
│ other) TreeEntries have a UserTreeIndices entry containing such an EdgeInfo.  │
│ Later code assumes EI.UserTE is non-null and dereferences it without checks,  │
│ leading to a segfault.                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug SLP log shows building several tree entries. No transformation is   │
│ applied yet; computeMinimumValueSizes is an analysis phase before cost        │
│ computation. The first transformation pass hit (segfault) happens while       │
│ evaluating predicates to determine bitwidth narrowing for the tree. There is  │
│ no IR modification yet, confirming the crash is due to incorrect analysis     │
│ assumptions (missing null checks) rather than a prior transformation          │
│ corrupting state.                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ EdgeInfo entries with null UserTE are inserted (e.g., via buildTree_rec with  │
│ EdgeInfo()). computeMinimumValueSizes attempts cycle detection and            │
│ classification of trunc/signed compare roots by iterating over                │
│ UserTreeIndices and performing operations like EI.UserTE->Idx,                │
│ EI.UserTE->getOpcode(), EI.UserTE->hasState(), and accessing                  │
│ EI.UserTE->Scalars. These dereferences lack a guard for EI.UserTE==nullptr.   │
│ When ExtraBitWidthNodes logic revisits NodeIdx==0 after the initial           │
│ early-return region, the subsequent IsTruncRoot and IsSignedCmp computations  │
│ dereference the null UserTE, triggering a segfault.                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Code locations needing fixes:                                                 │
│ - Cycle check lambda at lines 18183-18185: uses EI.UserTE->Idx without null   │
│ guard.                                                                        │
│ - IsTruncRoot lambda at lines 18460-18463: dereferences EI.UserTE             │
│ unconditionally.                                                              │
│ - IsSignedCmp lambda at lines 18469-18480: dereferences EI.UserTE and its     │
│ members unconditionally.                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit Point 1 (lines 18183-18185): Add a null check in the cycle detection     │
│ lambda to ensure EI.UserTE is non-null before accessing EI.UserTE->Idx.       │
│ Change:                                                                       │
│ return EI.UserTE->Idx > NodeIdx;                                              │
│ To:                                                                           │
│ return EI.UserTE && EI.UserTE->Idx > NodeIdx;                                 │
